  },
  {
    "client_msg_id": "be482ac0-da41-4b1a-a7b9-971c84793c18",
    "type": "message",
    "text": "I take the opposite view to <@UCUSW7WVD> — communities make or break a programming language. I might even tentatively propose that historically, language design has been secondary to social/cultural/community factors when it comes to success or failure (otherwise how could something like c++ or JS be so popular :wink:?) Though I think for end-users (and groups thereof) design matters a lot more than for developer-targeted languages, since clarity is paramount.",
    "user": "U6FKVSVCK",
    "ts": "1566240280.158200",
    "team": "T5TCAFTA9",
    "user_team": "T5TCAFTA9",
    "source_team": "T5TCAFTA9",
    "user_profile": {
      "avatar_hash": "cad501b70b26",
      "image_72": "https://avatars.slack-edge.com/2019-10-07/786673147216_cad501b70b26e7666ed0_72.png",
      "first_name": "Tim",
      "real_name": "Tim Babb",
      "display_name": "tbabb",
      "team": "T5TCAFTA9",
      "name": "tbabb",
      "is_restricted": false,
      "is_ultra_restricted": false
    },
    "edited": {
      "user": "U6FKVSVCK",
      "ts": "1566240375.000000"
    },
    "thread_ts": "1566238710.155700",
    "parent_user_id": "U5TCAFTD3",
    "channel_name": "of-end-user-programming",
    "channel_id": "CLYCGTCPL"
  },
  {
    "client_msg_id": "b04a8aa7-7e62-4495-a9af-ab74af24f74a",
    "type": "message",
    "text": "A healthy community is a very difficult thing to achieve and definitely doesn't happen by default!\n\nFWIW, I'll be making collaboration an important factor of my project.",
    "user": "U6FKVSVCK",
    "ts": "1566240346.158400",
    "team": "T5TCAFTA9",
    "user_team": "T5TCAFTA9",
    "source_team": "T5TCAFTA9",
    "user_profile": {
      "avatar_hash": "cad501b70b26",
      "image_72": "https://avatars.slack-edge.com/2019-10-07/786673147216_cad501b70b26e7666ed0_72.png",
      "first_name": "Tim",
      "real_name": "Tim Babb",
      "display_name": "tbabb",
      "team": "T5TCAFTA9",
      "name": "tbabb",
      "is_restricted": false,
      "is_ultra_restricted": false
    },
    "thread_ts": "1566238710.155700",
    "parent_user_id": "U5TCAFTD3",
    "reactions": [
      {
        "name": "+1",
        "users": [
          "UJ6LDMMN0",
          "UA14TGLTC"
        ],
        "count": 2
      }
    ],
    "channel_name": "of-end-user-programming",
    "channel_id": "CLYCGTCPL"
  },
  {
    "client_msg_id": "ad02e414-1421-40d8-876e-354dc6fbf8ca",
    "type": "message",
    "text": "To be clear, I'm only talking about the technical affordances for collaborating over software. We definitely need lots more for a healthy community, social norms and so on.",
    "user": "UCUSW7WVD",
    "ts": "1566240550.158700",
    "team": "T5TCAFTA9",
    "user_team": "T5TCAFTA9",
    "source_team": "T5TCAFTA9",
    "user_profile": {
      "avatar_hash": "6e649a383cf8",
      "image_72": "https://avatars.slack-edge.com/2019-07-14/687915485201_6e649a383cf8f9e366e3_72.png",
      "first_name": "Kartik",
      "real_name": "Kartik Agaram",
      "display_name": "",
      "team": "T5TCAFTA9",
      "name": "ak",
      "is_restricted": false,
      "is_ultra_restricted": false
    },
    "thread_ts": "1566238710.155700",
    "parent_user_id": "U5TCAFTD3",
    "channel_name": "of-end-user-programming",
    "channel_id": "CLYCGTCPL"
  },
  {
    "client_msg_id": "afc45549-7d5e-40cc-86bc-5e4777f0ad1a",
    "type": "message",
    "text": "Ah. I'd still say that matters a lot too, though— affordances can encourage/discourage trends in the community (including the tendency to share code or collaborate at all) by what it makes easy and what it makes difficult. Where to place or remove friction has a huge impact on how a community develops, especially given the nonlinearity of human interaction.",
    "user": "U6FKVSVCK",
    "ts": "1566240738.161000",
    "team": "T5TCAFTA9",
    "user_team": "T5TCAFTA9",
    "source_team": "T5TCAFTA9",
    "user_profile": {
      "avatar_hash": "cad501b70b26",
      "image_72": "https://avatars.slack-edge.com/2019-10-07/786673147216_cad501b70b26e7666ed0_72.png",
      "first_name": "Tim",
      "real_name": "Tim Babb",
      "display_name": "tbabb",
      "team": "T5TCAFTA9",
      "name": "tbabb",
      "is_restricted": false,
      "is_ultra_restricted": false
    },
    "thread_ts": "1566238710.155700",
    "parent_user_id": "U5TCAFTD3",
    "reactions": [
      {
        "name": "+1",
        "users": [
          "UJ6LDMMN0",
          "UA14TGLTC"
        ],
        "count": 2
      }
    ],
    "channel_name": "of-end-user-programming",
    "channel_id": "CLYCGTCPL"
  },
  {
    "client_msg_id": "c9eef62f-c25d-47f6-9ef0-7e07191e2be3",
    "type": "message",
    "text": "If there was a change I would make to the term it would be to drop \"end-user\". In the world I want to aim for there's no sharp difference between programmers and end-users. It's just a continuous spectrum of different people having different interests. X may take a little more time to make a change than Y, but there wouldn't be a stark binary distinction between experts and non-experts.\n\nOn the other hand, the current term benefits from being rooted in the world we have rather than the one we want. So the name is mostly fine.",
    "user": "UCUSW7WVD",
    "ts": "1566240883.164500",
    "team": "T5TCAFTA9",
    "user_team": "T5TCAFTA9",
    "source_team": "T5TCAFTA9",
    "user_profile": {
      "avatar_hash": "6e649a383cf8",
      "image_72": "https://avatars.slack-edge.com/2019-07-14/687915485201_6e649a383cf8f9e366e3_72.png",
      "first_name": "Kartik",
      "real_name": "Kartik Agaram",
      "display_name": "",
      "team": "T5TCAFTA9",
      "name": "ak",
      "is_restricted": false,
      "is_ultra_restricted": false
    },
    "reactions": [
      {
        "name": "+1",
        "users": [
          "U6FKVSVCK",
          "UE6EFEPTQ",
          "UA14TGLTC",
          "UEP7RL0HX",
          "UGK6P07UP",
